{\pos(196,180)}纸牌屋

64
00:03:57,340 --> 00:04:00,300
{\an2}{\pos(211.4,243.6)}第三季  第三集

65
00:04:12,390 --> 00:04:15,690
约旦河谷只是树木  我们不能不见森林
The Jordan Valley is the trees instead of the forest.

66
00:04:15,790 --> 00:04:18,940
而这个双边政策  是在疏远我们
And this bilateral approach, it's... alienating.

67
00:04:19,450 --> 00:04:22,390
我跟卡斯皮女士并不总能达成一致
I don't often see eye to eye with Ms. Caspi,

68
00:04:22,390 --> 00:04:26,230
但你们似乎是在要求巴勒斯坦
but it does feel like you're asking the state of Palestine

69
00:04:26,230 --> 00:04:29,050
支持一项我们不能参与商议制定的计划
to support a plan without having a seat at the table.

70
00:04:29,940 --> 00:04:32,530
我们的目标是软化俄罗斯
Well, our goal is to soften Russia,

71
00:04:32,530 --> 00:04:34,520
先让他们作为合作伙伴加入
to bring them in as a partner first--

72
00:04:34,520 --> 00:04:38,320
如果能说服俄国组建联合部队
If we can get the Russians to agree to a joint force,

73
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:41,560
一起监控约旦河谷  他们会加入的
monitor the valley together, then they're invested.

74
00:04:41,730 --> 00:04:43,670
之后他们就不会阻碍我们...
They won't be a thorn in our side when we move forward--

75
00:04:43,670 --> 00:04:45,550
我们能指望俄罗斯吗
How can we count on the Russians?

76
00:04:46,170 --> 00:04:48,940
你丈夫真认为佩特罗夫信得过吗
Does your husband truly believe he can trust Petrov?

77
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:52,240
总统很乐观
The president is optimistic.

78
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:54,860
我们只希望你们愿意考虑
All we ask is that you remain open-minded.

79
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:57,080
希望你把
I hope you'll convey our

80
00:04:57,080 --> 00:04:59,420
我们的不满直接传达给你丈夫
dissatisfaction directly to your husband.

81
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,460
我一定转达你们的担忧
I'll be sure to share your concerns.

82
00:05:01,460 --> 00:05:04,490
安德伍德大使会跟你们保持联络的
Ambassador Underwood will remain in contact with both of you.

83
00:05:15,380 --> 00:05:17,180
之前不该插你的话
I shouldn't have interrupted you earlier.

84
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:20,300
会面时  太不应该了
In the meeting. It was out of place,

85
00:05:20,300 --> 00:05:22,490
我该让你说的
and I should have let you do all the talking.

86
00:05:22,490 --> 00:05:23,460
没事的
It's fine.

87
00:05:25,990 --> 00:05:27,640
我知道你对我有怀疑
I know you have doubts about me.

88
00:05:28,710 --> 00:05:31,340
休会任命的事  我们还没谈过
The recess appointment. We haven't discussed it.

89
00:05:31,380 --> 00:05:33,550
-应该谈谈的  -真的没必要
- And we should. - It really isn't necessary.

90
00:05:34,370 --> 00:05:36,750
这的确不合常规
It is an unorthodox dynamic, yes.

91
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:38,090
你也总归是第一夫人
You will always be the First Lady.

92
00:05:38,090 --> 00:05:41,060
这也是你的飞机  但我们能处理好
This is your plane, after all. But we can work around that.

93
00:05:41,060 --> 00:05:43,530
我知道  但我想告诉你...
Yes, I know, but I want you to know that--

94
00:05:43,980 --> 00:05:46,210
安德伍德夫人  总统来电
Mrs. Underwood, the president is on the line.

95
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:58,050
怎么样
How'd it go?

96
00:05:58,050 --> 00:06:00,130
-要接通凯茜吗  -不  直接跟我说
- Should we conference Cathy in? - No, just tell me.

97
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:02,240
有很对反对  他们不满意
A lot of pushback. They aren't happy.

98
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:04,350
等时机成熟  他们就会同意
Well, they'll get on board when the time comes.

99
00:06:04,350 --> 00:06:06,590
-你那边怎么样  -他说不
- What about you? - He said no.

100
00:06:06,590 --> 00:06:09,230
-这是他嘴里冒出的第一个字  -全盘拒绝吗
- First word out of his mouth. - No to everything?

101
00:06:09,230 --> 00:06:10,820
他可能只是玩心理战
Oh, he might just be playing mind games,

102
00:06:10,820 --> 00:06:12,160
让我自乱脚
trying to throw me off balance,

103
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,860
但他毕竟是克格勃出身
but this is a guy who was brought up through the KGB, after all.

104
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:17,040
你和凯茜出手得温柔点
We're gonna have to have you and Cathy use the light touch.

105
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:18,230
我们得软磨硬泡
We need to massage this.

106
00:06:18,230 --> 00:06:19,700
我们接通凯茜吧
Let's include her in this phone call.

107
00:06:19,700 --> 00:06:21,580
不  你直接告诉她  我马上要会面了
No, just tell her. I have to go in soon.

108
00:06:21,690 --> 00:06:23,440
不直接告诉她很不好
It's important we don't bypass her.

109
00:06:23,440 --> 00:06:26,310
好像我们有意不跟她通气  弗兰西斯
If it looks like we're leaving her out of the loop, Francis...

110
00:06:26,310 --> 00:06:27,530
行  接通她
All right, put her on.

111
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:29,690
我无法形容这对我们团队是多么重要
I can't tell you how much it would mean to the team.

112
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:32,750
能有您这样履历的专业人士加入
To have your qualifications, your expertise on board.

113
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:34,970
光是把您的名字摆在网页上就够风光了
Even just having your name on the website.

114
00:06:35,020 --> 00:06:36,960
很感激您这么说  议员先生
I appreciate your saying that, Congressman.

115
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:39,900
请叫我布拉德  实习生才叫我议员先生
Brad. Please. Congressman's what the interns call me.

116
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,610
行  就叫布拉德
All right. Brad it is.

117
00:06:41,730 --> 00:06:44,570
至于您的头衔  特别顾问行吗
Now as for your title, I was thinking Special Advisor?

118
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:46,960
-头衔不重要  -随您怎么叫
- Title doesn't matter to me. - You pick what you want.

119
00:06:47,310 --> 00:06:49,620
工作时间您说了算  想来就来  想走就走
And you make your own hours. Come and go as you like.

120
00:06:50,150 --> 00:06:52,880
22万美元一年怎么样
Uh, compensation, would 220 a year work for you?

121
00:06:54,130 --> 00:06:55,980
上限是17.3万
The cap is 173.

122
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:58,750
另外五万从我的改选资金里拨
Well, the extra 50K would come out of my re-election fund.

123
00:06:59,270 --> 00:07:01,060
只拿最高工资不是亏待了您
I mean, you deserve more than the cap.

124
00:07:02,010 --> 00:07:03,220
您的提议很慷慨
That's a very generous offer.

125
00:07:03,220 --> 00:07:04,480
希望您能付出等价努力
Well, I expect you to earn it.

126
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:07,220
这次竞选我很想有所作为
I really want to make my mark this session.

127
00:07:07,220 --> 00:07:09,520
-比安德伍德付的还多  -什么
- That's more than Underwood paid me. - I'm sorry?

128
00:07:10,380 --> 00:07:12,530
我当他的幕僚长时  拿最高工资  
When I was his chief of staff, I made the cap.

129
00:07:13,190 --> 00:07:14,910
他给的远不到22万
He never came anywhere near 220.

130
00:07:14,910 --> 00:07:16,070
我说过  我觉得您该...
Well, like I said, I think you deserve--

131
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:17,730
工资太高了  议员先生
It's too much money, Congressman.

132
00:07:18,470 --> 00:07:19,760
我不觉得  但是
Well, I disagree, but,

133
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:22,160
您想拿少点我不反对
hey, I'm not gonna argue if you want to get paid less.

134
00:07:23,190 --> 00:07:24,710
我说了  这份运输法案
As I was saying, this transpo bill,

135
00:07:24,710 --> 00:07:27,090
能产生很大的影响
we really have an opportunity to make a difference.

136
00:07:35,940 --> 00:07:37,750
女士们  先生们  会面结束
Ladies and gentlemen, the session is over.

137
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:40,610
请往这边走  谢谢前来
Please, right this way. Thank you for coming.

138
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:49,550
我听说您最近开始冲浪了
I hear you've recently taken up surfing.

139
00:07:50,850 --> 00:07:53,230
黑海那边有几个地方不错
We have a few spots on the Black Sea.

140
00:07:53,230 --> 00:07:55,310
主要是我能摆姿势拍照
It's mostly so I can pose for the photos.

141
00:07:55,540 --> 00:07:56,850
是  我看到照片了
Yes, I've seen them.

142
00:07:59,170 --> 00:08:01,130
年轻人喜欢
It plays well with the young people.

143
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,890
让他们看到自己的总统有点乐趣很重要
It's important they see their president has some fun,

144
00:08:03,890 --> 00:08:05,720
不会把自己搞得太严肃
doesn't take himself too seriously.

145
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,050
我给你准备了份礼物
I have a gift for you.

146
00:08:14,350 --> 00:08:16,650
抱歉来晚了
I'm sorry for the delay.

147
00:08:16,850 --> 00:08:19,380
希望没让你们等太久
I hope we didn't keep you waiting too long.

148
00:08:22,290 --> 00:08:23,140
可以开始了吗
Shall we?

149
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:28,050
这是托马斯·吴亲手做的  很有才的美国手艺人
This was handmade by Tomas Vu, a very talented American artist.

150
00:08:28,230 --> 00:08:31,960
一面用激光刻了画  另一面
He laser-etches images on one side, and on the other side...

151
00:08:32,890 --> 00:08:34,580
是披头士的歌词
he puts Beatles lyrics.

152
00:08:37,050 --> 00:08:38,390
回到苏联时期了
Back in the USSR.

153
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:41,000
这是博物馆藏品  但你还是能用它冲浪
It's a museum piece, but you can still ride it.

154
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:43,510
你什么来我索契的乡间别墅吧
You should come out to my dacha in Sochi sometime.

155
00:08:43,830 --> 00:08:44,870
我们可以一起冲浪
We'll surf together.

156
00:08:45,580 --> 00:08:49,470
水冷得刺骨  但当地女人很热情
The water is cold as hell, but... the women are very warm.

157
00:08:49,470 --> 00:08:51,720
克莱尔怕是不会乐意
Oh, I'm not sure what Claire would think about that.

158
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:53,800
带她一起
Well, bring her along.

159
00:08:54,780 --> 00:08:56,430
那里有很多艺术家
It's crawling with artists out there.

160
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:58,260
说不定她能找到喜欢的
She might find something she likes.

161
00:09:01,540 --> 00:09:03,160
总统先生  我很好奇
Mr. President, I'm intrigued.

162
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:06,150
你一到美国对我说的第一个字就是"不"
The first thing you say to me is "No" the second you arrive,

163
00:09:06,150 --> 00:09:08,390
紧接着又邀请我去你的乡间别墅
and the next moment you're inviting me to your dacha.

164
00:09:09,180 --> 00:09:10,370
你到底是个什么样的人
Who am I dealing with?

165
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:13,900
我刚来就说清楚了  你有什么疑惑
I believe I was clear when we first met. What confuses you?

166
00:09:13,900 --> 00:09:16,420
我们的代表团谈这些事谈了好几个月
Our delegations have been discussing these issues for months.

167
00:09:16,420 --> 00:09:18,930
没错  但谈不代表达成一致
Yes, but discussions are not the same as commitment.

168
00:09:19,610 --> 00:09:21,240
我现在告诉你
And, uh, I'm telling you now.

169
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,670
我们不会达成一致
There will be no commitment.

170
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:26,200
这你打电话就能告诉我了
You could've told me that on the phone.

171
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:32,390
我以为你邀我来是想弥补对我的侮辱
I assumed you were undoing an insult by having me here.

172
00:09:32,660 --> 00:09:34,100
什么侮辱
What insult is that?

173
00:09:34,390 --> 00:09:37,050
你的前两任都没邀请我来过华盛顿
Two of your predecessors never invited me to Washington.

174
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:39,290
这次峰会不是走过场
This summit is not just for show.

175
00:09:39,380 --> 00:09:41,740
我希望能朝着和平的目标迈出一大步
I want to make meaningful strides toward peace.

176
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:44,720
历史告诉我们  中东地区是没救了
The Middle East is hopeless. History tells us that.

177
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:47,300
我是在给你创造历史的机会
I'm offering you the chance to make history.

178
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:48,430
我就跟你说实话了
I'll be honest with you,

179
00:09:48,430 --> 00:09:50,850
毕竟你好心好意请我来
because you've been kind enough to invite me to your country.

180
00:09:52,830 --> 00:09:56,190
中东和平  对俄罗斯毫无利益可言
Russia has nothing to gain from peace in the Middle East.

181
00:09:56,340 --> 00:10:00,560
更重要的是  和美国合作也毫无利益
And more importantly, nothing to gain from working with America.

182
00:10:01,890 --> 00:10:04,290
以色列一向不信任我们
Israel has always distrusted us.

183
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:05,750
你指望这有所改变吗
You expect that to change?

184
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:08,040
我们希望能慢慢建立信任
We expect to build trust over time.

185
00:10:10,450 --> 00:10:13,100
你们今早和大使们的会面怎么样
How was your meeting with the ambassadors this morning?

186
00:10:14,290 --> 00:10:16,160
阿鲁里大使给我打电话了
Ambassador Aruri called me.

187
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:18,180
他们有疑虑
They have their doubts,

188
00:10:18,180 --> 00:10:20,450
但我们希望他们能愿意考虑
but we encouraged them to keep an open mind.

189
00:10:20,450 --> 00:10:22,020
他说他十分担忧
He described it as grave concerns.

190
00:10:22,020 --> 00:10:23,840
等我们确定了他们自然会适应...
They will acclimate as soon as we establish--

191
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:27,470
你丈夫直接向以色列和巴勒斯坦提议了吗
Has your husband made direct overtures to Israel and Palestine?

192
00:10:27,770 --> 00:10:29,320
所有正式通讯
All formal communication

193
00:10:29,330 --> 00:10:31,330
都经由国务院处理
has been handled through the State Department.

194
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:33,620
但你丈夫不可能认为他们会顺从吧
But your husband can't possibly believe they'll comply.

195
00:10:33,620 --> 00:10:35,350
先生们  为了让谈话进行下去
Gentlemen, for the purposes of these talks,

196
00:10:35,350 --> 00:10:37,520
请你们叫他总统
I'd appreciate it if you refer to him as the president,

197
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:38,930
而不是"我丈夫"
not as my husband.

198
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:40,650
当然  大使女士
Of course, Madam Ambassador.

199
00:10:40,650 --> 00:10:42,770
而且你该向杜兰特国务卿发问
And you really should be addressing Secretary Durant.

200
00:10:42,770 --> 00:10:45,540
她比我更能代表总统的意见
She speaks on his behalf more than I do.

201
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:50,080
抱歉  国务卿女士  请继续吧
Our apologies, Madam Secretary. Please, continue.

202
00:10:50,470 --> 00:10:55,520
我们想把细节梳理完  请翻到12页
We'd like to finish reviewing the specifics, so page 12, please.

203
00:10:55,830 --> 00:10:58,950
总统先生  我们已经在多个方面展开了合作
Mr. President, we're already working together on several fronts:

204
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:02,040
防核扩散协议  打击恐怖主义  朝鲜
nonproliferation, the War on Terror, North Korea.

205
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:04,620
为什么中东就偏偏不行呢
I don't see any reason that the Middle East should be any different.

206
00:11:04,620 --> 00:11:07,020
-因为这是美国的计划  -不是那样
- Because it's an American plan. - It's not an American plan.

207
00:11:07,020 --> 00:11:09,550
-我保证条件平等  -保证
- I'm promising equal terms. - Oh, promises.

208
00:11:09,550 --> 00:11:11,000
卡特总统保证双方平等参与
Carter promised equal involvement,

209
00:11:09,550 --> 00:11:12,270
{\pos(382,284)}{\an3}1978年在戴维营军事基地
卡特总统促成埃及与以色列之间
签署了《戴维营协议》

210
00:11:11,010 --> 00:11:12,270
最后签协议的时候却没叫我们
then shut us out of Camp David.

211
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:13,860
波斯尼亚战争  克林顿也是如此
Clinton did the same with Bosnia.

212
00:11:13,860 --> 00:11:14,970
现在我是总统
I'm the president now.

213
00:11:14,980 --> 00:11:16,400
这次不会那样了
That won't happen this time.

214
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:19,080
直到18个月之后  你下台
Until 18 months from now, when you are replaced.

215
00:11:22,590 --> 00:11:23,990
我很嫉妒  维克多
I'm jealous, Viktor.

216
00:11:25,820 --> 00:11:29,170
你不用向任何人汇报  没有任何对手
You don't answer to anyone. You have no real opposition.

217
00:11:29,170 --> 00:11:32,230
你也知道大选结果会怎么样
You know exactly how every election is gonna turn out.

218
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:35,040
美国可不是这样
Well, it's not like that in the United States.

219
00:11:35,540 --> 00:11:37,800
我不竞选  是因为我
I'm not running because I can

220
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:41,250
能做到总统候选人做不到的事  比如这份提议
do things a candidate can't do, like this proposal.

221
00:11:41,260 --> 00:11:43,820
得了吧  总统先生  你我都知道你会参选的
Please, Mr. President, we both know you'll run.

222
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:48,710
不过能不能赢  谁知道呢
Now, whether you win... Who knows?

223
00:11:49,020 --> 00:11:51,700
直说吧  你究竟想要什么
Brass tacks. If you could have anything, what would it be?

224
00:11:54,370 --> 00:11:56,280
我没什么想要的
I came with nothing to ask.

225
00:11:57,710 --> 00:12:00,880
你这种人如果没有胃口  是不会赴宴的
Men like you don't show up for dinner without an appetite.

226
00:12:05,940 --> 00:12:08,360
我旅途劳顿  总统先生
It was a long flight, Mr. President.

227
00:12:09,730 --> 00:12:11,000
先谈到这儿吧
How about we stop here for now.

228
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,170
我休息休息眼睛
I rest my eyes a bit and

229
00:12:12,170 --> 00:12:14,340
等精神好点再想想这个提案
put some thought into this with a fresh mind.

230
00:12:15,650 --> 00:12:19,190
没准能想出我要什么
Maybe I'll... think of something I want.

231
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:21,720
等晚宴的时候再谈
We'll talk more later, at dinner.

232
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:23,520
可以啊  如果你想这样
Of course, if that's what you prefer.

233
00:12:26,610 --> 00:12:29,310
他知道自己要什么  就是要别人求他
He knows exactly what he wants, but he needs to be wooed.

234
00:12:29,310 --> 00:12:30,840
不过也算有进展
Progress, nonetheless.

235
00:12:31,140 --> 00:12:34,110
不经过"也许"  是没法把"不"变成"好"的
You can't turn a "No" to a "Yes" without a "maybe" in between.

236
00:12:44,170 --> 00:12:44,990
先生们
Gentlemen...

237
00:12:45,860 --> 00:12:47,520
副局长来了
Deputy Director coming through.

238
00:13:24,590 --> 00:13:27,140
奥尔西  跟我来
Orsay? Come with me, please.

239
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,210
我们抓到亚设了
We got Asher.

240
00:13:29,900 --> 00:13:32,030
凌晨两点半  他要吓死了
Two-thirty this morning. He was scared to death.

241
00:13:32,590 --> 00:13:35,660
15分钟之后  他给了我们6TB的压缩文件
By 2:45, he gave us six terabytes of compressed files.

242
00:13:35,660 --> 00:13:37,950
两千五百万美国电话电报公司用户的信息
All 25 million AT&T users.

243
00:13:38,270 --> 00:13:39,870
你的货存错地方了
You hid your goodies with the wrong person.

244
00:13:39,870 --> 00:13:42,100
-不止他一个  -我觉得就他一个
- He wasn't the only one. - I think he was.

245
00:13:43,130 --> 00:13:45,720
我的指控已经撤销了  你没法逮捕我
You can't arrest me for charges that have already been dropped.

246
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:47,670
放松  没人要逮捕你
Relax. No one's arresting you.

247
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:50,170
从我手上的报告看
From the reports I've been getting,

248
00:13:50,170 --> 00:13:52,120
你工作一直很出色
you've been doing an excellent job for us.

249
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:55,520
好好继续干下去  前途无量
If you stay straight, sky's the limit.

250
00:13:56,390 --> 00:13:57,660
接大任务  领导自己的团队
Bigger assignments. Manage your own team.

251
00:13:57,660 --> 00:13:59,110
你知道我也是走投无路才来的
You know I wouldn't be here if I had a choice.

252
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:00,650
但你现在有选择了
But you do have a choice.

253
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:04,810
你可以充分利用这第二次机会
You can make the most of this second chance if you want to,

254
00:14:04,810 --> 00:14:08,640
但你得证明你想要这机会
but... you have to prove you want it.

255
00:14:10,430 --> 00:14:12,890
-名字  -我不求别的
- Names. - That's all I've ever wanted.

256
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:15,140
不行
No.

257
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:21,130
亚设会供出名字的
Asher's going to give up names.

258
00:14:22,640 --> 00:14:24,340
-他不会那么做的  -或许会
- He wouldn't do that. - He might.

259
00:14:25,050 --> 00:14:25,990
但愿他们不会抖出些
Let's hope none of them tell us

260
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:28,170
我们还不知道的你的罪行
about anything we didn't charge you for.

261
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:34,010
你在这里可以有大好未来  嘉文
You have a future here, Gavin.

262
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:39,120
好了  回去吧
All right. Back to it.

263
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:43,700
好好工作
Keep up the good work.

264
00:14:45,390 --> 00:14:47,200
我们得去晚宴了
We have to wine and dine.

265
00:14:47,510 --> 00:14:50,230
-要迷倒他们  -他们  还有谁
- Charm them senseless. - Them? Who's the other?

266
00:14:50,230 --> 00:14:53,670
博奇  他压着《美就法》不肯动弹
Birch. He's sitting on AmWorks like his ass is afraid of the sun.

267
00:14:53,670 --> 00:14:55,580
别逼我跟鲍勃聊天
Please don't make me talk to Bob.

268
00:14:55,580 --> 00:14:58,190
你只用负责佩特罗夫  我来对付鲍勃
You just focus on Petrov. I'll deal with Bob.

269
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:00,690
打扰一下  先生  我们准备好了
Excuse me, sir. We're all set.

270
00:15:00,690 --> 00:15:02,430
佩特罗夫总统在黄色椭圆厅了
President Petrov is in the Yellow Oval.

271
00:15:02,430 --> 00:15:03,690
谢谢  卡莉斯塔
Thank you, Calista.

272
00:15:07,410 --> 00:15:10,000
我可能需要弥补一下凯茜
I think I may need to do some damage control with Cathy.

273
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:12,350
-为什么  -我一直努力对她恭敬
- Why? - I've been trying to be deferential,

274
00:15:12,350 --> 00:15:15,150
但她可能觉得我是自视高她一等
but I think it's coming off as patronizing.

275
00:15:15,610 --> 00:15:18,300
-本就有这风险  -我知道
- Well, that was the risk. - I know.

276
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:19,880
她觉得受威胁了吗
Is she feeling threatened?

277
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:22,880
威胁  不会  可能有点被抢了风头
Threatened, no. Possibly overshadowed.

278
00:15:23,460 --> 00:15:24,750
我的关注度太高
I think I'm getting too much attention

279
00:15:24,750 --> 00:15:27,010
凯茜不跟我一队
and it's tough to be effective

280
00:15:27,010 --> 00:15:28,280
我会举步维艰
when I don't have Cathy on my team,

281
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:30,060
我可能得讨她欢心
so I may need to win her over.

282
00:15:30,330 --> 00:15:32,650
别忘了今晚的主角应该是谁
Well, let's not forget where the focus is tonight.

283
00:15:33,150 --> 00:15:35,410
我什么时候不能一心二用了
Since when can't I do two things at once?

284
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:37,930
-你歪了  -什么
- You're crooked. - What?

285
00:15:40,890 --> 00:15:43,670
-准备好去战斗了吗  -是的
- Ready for battle. - Yes.

286
00:16:21,850 --> 00:16:23,760
美利坚合众国副总统  唐纳德·布莱斯
The Vice President of the United States, Donald Blythe.

287
00:16:23,760 --> 00:16:25,730
-总统先生  欢迎  -副总统先生
- Mr. President. Welcome. - Mr. Vice President.

288
00:16:25,730 --> 00:16:26,590
谢谢
Thank you.

289
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:30,120
佩特罗夫总统  欢迎
President Petrov, welcome.

290
00:16:30,120 --> 00:16:31,040
倍感荣幸
It's a pleasure.

291
00:16:34,020 --> 00:16:34,820
你美极了
You look beautiful.

292
00:16:34,820 --> 00:16:36,440
马马虎虎吧
Oh, it's serviceable.

293
00:16:36,730 --> 00:16:39,120
-你也和往常一样明艳动人  -谢谢
- You look fantastic, as always. - Thank you.

294
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:42,750
大家的注意力都会在你身上  不是他们
All eyes at the table will be on you, not them.

295
00:16:44,380 --> 00:16:47,430
门多萨参议员  不久就是总统候选人了
Senator Mendoza. Soon to be candidate Mendoza.

296
00:16:47,430 --> 00:16:48,700
这就谣言四起了
The rumor mill begins.

297
00:16:48,700 --> 00:16:50,940
你最开始是跟着里根  对吗
You started with Reagan, no?

298
00:16:50,950 --> 00:16:52,500
他84年竞选团队的一员
Staffed on his '84 campaign.

299
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:55,770
他办公室里有张里根总统戴牛仔帽的照片
He has a portrait of the Gipper in his office wearing a cowboy hat.

300
00:16:56,660 --> 00:16:57,860
那时男人还有男子气概
When men were men.

301
00:17:03,370 --> 00:17:04,400
鲍勃  我有个想法
Bob, I had a thought.

302
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:06,240
大卫·布兰切特在军事委员会
Dave Blanchek is on Armed Services and--

303
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:07,860
我不想让后面的人久等
I don't want to hold up the line.

304
00:17:09,550 --> 00:17:12,010
-总统先生  很荣幸  -移下博奇的位置
- Mr. President, a pleasure. - I want to move Birch.

305
00:17:12,010 --> 00:17:13,840
门多萨换到我边上来
Put Mendoza next to me instead.

306
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:16,580
艾伦  收拾得挺利索
Alan. You clean up well.

307
00:17:16,840 --> 00:17:18,230
场合需要
Class by association.

308
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:20,380
-你的女伴呢  -我一个人来的
- Where's your date? - I don't have one.

309
00:17:20,380 --> 00:17:22,070
你想得话  我可以陪你走进去
I can walk you in too, if you'd like.

310
00:17:22,070 --> 00:17:23,950
不了  那不是要毁了你的照片
No. Wouldn't want to ruin the picture.

311
00:17:26,370 --> 00:17:27,730
我们的特殊客人
Ah, our special guests.

312
00:17:27,730 --> 00:17:29,390
很高兴你们能参加晚宴
I'm so delighted you could be with us.

313
00:17:29,390 --> 00:17:31,520
感谢你们能来  总统先生
Thank you so much for coming. Mr. President.

314
00:17:31,490 --> 00:17:34,370
{\pos(189.4,234.4)}{\pos(193,238)}过了这么久才有机会在同一张桌子上坐下

315
00:17:34,450 --> 00:17:38,700
{\pos(190.4,234.4)}{\pos(193,238)}你们在闭门会议时讨论了我们的问题吗

316
00:17:38,790 --> 00:17:40,120
{\pos(190.9,251.5)}{\pos(193,238)}我们讨论了很多事

317
00:17:40,210 --> 00:17:43,250
{\pos(190.9,251.5)}{\pos(193,238)}但我们的担忧呢

318
00:17:43,270 --> 00:17:45,420
我们列出的问题你们谈过了吗
Was anything on our list discussed?

319
00:17:45,420 --> 00:17:47,700
-先照相吧  -好主意
- Why don't we take a photo first? - Good idea. Hm?

320
00:17:59,140 --> 00:18:00,560
{\pos(190.8,219.6)}{\pos(190.8,221.85)}门多萨先生

321
00:18:02,100 --> 00:18:04,810
{\pos(197.7,221.85)}{\pos(190.8,221.85)}博奇先生

322
00:18:08,710 --> 00:18:11,260
维克多  告诉我  你在恋爱吗
Viktor, tell me. Are you in love?

323
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:14,770
爱什么的我不知道
I don't know about... love, but...

324
00:18:17,030 --> 00:18:19,240
但我在学习享受离婚的乐趣
I'm learning to enjoy being divorced.

325
00:18:22,410 --> 00:18:23,630
欢迎来到美国
Добро пожаловать!

326
00:18:23,930 --> 00:18:26,030
感谢你们的光临
Спасибо, что вы пришли.

327
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:29,020
翻译过来就是
Which translates into:

328
00:18:29,020 --> 00:18:31,750
"你好  请别偷银器"
"Howdy, and please don't steal the silverware."

329
00:18:34,430 --> 00:18:37,230
卖弄完了我会说的所有俄语之后
Now that I have exhausted all of the Russian I know,

330
00:18:37,670 --> 00:18:40,390
克莱尔和我想欢迎大家来到白宫
Claire and I would like to welcome all of you to the White House,

331
00:18:40,840 --> 00:18:43,110
很荣幸能在这次历史性的国事访问中
as we host President Petrov

332
00:18:43,290 --> 00:18:45,750
招待佩特罗夫总统
in this historic state visit.

333
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:49,220
一个世纪前  一个半世纪前
A century ago, a century and a half ago,

334
00:18:49,710 --> 00:18:50,900
{\pos(234,284)}{\an1}法国历史学家  政治家
政治社会学的奠基人

335
00:18:49,710 --> 00:18:50,900
德·托克维尔
de Tocqueville wrote,

336
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:54,380
对于美国和俄国的看法是这样
in regards to America and Russia, the following:

337
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:58,550
"他们的出发点和道路不同
"Their point of departure and their paths diverse,

338
00:18:58,550 --> 00:19:01,640
可是  两国似乎都
nevertheless, each seems called

339
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:05,460
受到了天意的秘密召唤
by some secret desire of providence,

340
00:19:05,620 --> 00:19:10,850
终有一天要将半个世界的命运掌握在自己手里"
to one day hold in their hands the destinies of half the world."

341
00:19:10,850 --> 00:19:13,350
今晚我想做点修改
Well, I'd like to amend that tonight and say,

342
00:19:13,350 --> 00:19:14,920
并不只是半个世界
not just half the world,

343
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:19,400
全球都指望我们的领导
the entire world looks to us for leadership.

344
00:19:19,420 --> 00:19:21,960
让我们敬佩特罗夫总统
So, to President Petrov,

345
00:19:22,420 --> 00:19:23,820
以及我们两个伟大国家
and all of the great things

346
00:19:23,820 --> 00:19:26,510
精诚合作将创造的美好未来
that our great nations will do together.

347
00:19:26,670 --> 00:19:29,010
-敬总统先生  -说得好
- Mr. President. - Hear, hear!

348
00:19:33,630 --> 00:19:35,730
永远别给法国人机会
Никогда не добрай францусзам.

349
00:19:36,220 --> 00:19:39,030
翻译过来就是  "永远不要相信法国人"
Which is Russian for, "Never trust the French."

350
00:19:41,520 --> 00:19:42,620
总统先生和第一夫人
And thank you to the President

351
00:19:42,630 --> 00:19:45,590
感谢你们热情周到的招待
and First Lady for your grace and hospitality.

352
00:19:45,810 --> 00:19:48,350
比德·托克维尔时代更晚一点
Now, a little more recently than de Tocqueville,

353
00:19:48,350 --> 00:19:50,470
大概三十年前
about, uh, 30 years ago,

354
00:19:51,210 --> 00:19:53,740
米哈伊尔·戈尔巴乔夫来到白宫
Mikhail Gorbachev came to this very House

355
00:19:53,740 --> 00:19:57,100
谈到为两国之间的"不满之冬"划上句号
and talked of an end to our "Winter of discontent."

356
00:19:58,660 --> 00:20:02,920
我认为现在可以说那段寒冬早已结束
I think it's safe to say that that winter seems far gone now.

357
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:05,960
而现在  在这个醉人的五月夜晚
And here, on this beautiful May evening,

358
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:09,120
我迎来了这个"迷人之春"
I welcome a "Spring of enchantment."

359
00:20:09,380 --> 00:20:13,220
我们都明白它的魅力从何而来
Now we all know which of you brings the enchantment to the table.

360
00:20:14,270 --> 00:20:15,760
敬您  安德伍德夫人
To you, Mrs. Underwood.

361
00:20:19,530 --> 00:20:23,100
-当然  也敬您的丈夫  -谢谢
- And, of course, your lesser half. - Ah, thank you.

362
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:31,280
我还想敬这里的另外三位贵宾
Now I'd like to toast three others in this room tonight.

363
00:20:31,820 --> 00:20:35,420
娜迪亚·托伦科尼卡瓦  玛莎·艾柳金纳
Nadya Tolokonnikova, Masha Alyokhina,

364
00:20:35,420 --> 00:20:36,610
和彼得·韦奇洛夫
and Pyotr Verzilov.

365
00:20:37,620 --> 00:20:39,860
我知道我们政见有分歧
Now, I know we had our differences.

366
00:20:40,180 --> 00:20:43,860
但我也知道我们的出发点都一样
But I also know they come from something we all share:

367
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:48,240
那就是对我们祖国深深的爱
a deep love of our country.

368
00:20:50,210 --> 00:20:52,820
敬你们  也敬俄罗斯
To you. And to Russia.

369
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:58,000
总统先生  娜迪亚和玛莎想致辞
Mr. President, Nadya and Masha would like to make a toast.

370
00:20:58,030 --> 00:21:00,530
敬俄罗斯总统维克多·佩特罗夫
За Виктора Ивановича Петрова, президента России

371
00:21:00,530 --> 00:21:02,230
对朋友如此义气
который так умеет дружить,

372
00:21:02,230 --> 00:21:05,130
-甚至把半个国家拱手相送  -敬维克多·佩特罗夫
- что подарил своим друзьям полстраны! - To Viktor Petrov,

373
00:21:05,130 --> 00:21:07,460
他对祖国如此忠诚  以至要将半个国家
whose loyalty runs so deep he's given his friends

374
00:21:07,460 --> 00:21:09,430
-拱手让于他人  -他是如此尊敬异己者
- half of the country. - Который так уважает критиков

375
00:21:09,430 --> 00:21:10,950
让他们都进了大牢
что посадил всех критиков в тюрьму!

376
00:21:10,950 --> 00:21:12,220
他开明地接受批评
Who's so open to criticism,

377
00:21:12,220 --> 00:21:14,010
以至于大多批评他的人都已入狱
that most of his critics are in prison.

378
00:21:14,010 --> 00:21:17,530
敬最高统帅维克多·佩特罗夫
За Виктора Пертова, Верховного Главнокомандующего,

379
00:21:17,530 --> 00:21:19,730
他什么都不怕  却害怕同性恋者
которому не страшен никто! Кроме геев.

380
00:21:19,730 --> 00:21:20,430
够了
Хватить!

381
00:21:22,560 --> 00:21:23,810
你们的意思已经很明白了
You made your point.

382
00:21:25,220 --> 00:21:30,160
现在  请坐吧  让我们大家
Now, please, sit and let us all

383
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:32,900
像真正的俄罗斯人那样开怀畅饮
drink and laugh, like true Russians do.

384
00:21:46,520 --> 00:21:48,730
总统先生
Well, Mr. President,

385
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:51,550
这就证明你们不要孩子
this is proof why you made the right decision

386
00:21:51,550 --> 00:21:52,940
是多么明智的决定
never to have children.

387
00:22:01,090 --> 00:22:02,850
我的手下跟他们交待过
My staff prepped them.

388
00:22:02,850 --> 00:22:04,770
-他们向我们做了保证  -没关系
- They assured us. - It's nothing.

389
00:22:05,420 --> 00:22:08,260
-我敬佩你的胸襟  -没关系  无需多言
- I admire your grace. - Please. Not another word.

390
00:22:10,450 --> 00:22:12,420
我就知道请暴动小猫不是个好主意
I knew Pussy Riot was a bad idea.

391
00:22:12,940 --> 00:22:13,920
你该去处理
You should go.

392
00:22:13,960 --> 00:22:15,910
不  最好的处理就是不作评论
No. Best thing is not to comment.

393
00:22:15,910 --> 00:22:17,330
否则我们会沦为跟他们一个档次
It lowers us to their level.

394
00:22:19,350 --> 00:22:20,450
喝果汁还是汽水
Juice or soda?

395
00:22:21,040 --> 00:22:22,740
低热量的就行  如果你有的话
Diet something, if you got it.

396
00:22:23,940 --> 00:22:24,830
照片上是谁
Who are they?

397
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:30,290
我哥哥的孩子
My brother's kids.

398
00:22:31,900 --> 00:22:32,850
挺可爱的
Adorable.

399
00:22:40,740 --> 00:22:41,910
我收到一个工作邀请
I got a job offer.

400
00:22:42,710 --> 00:22:43,620
是吗  哪里
Yeah? Where?

401
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:46,380
布拉德·帕蒂特的特别顾问
Brad Petite. Special Advisor.

402
00:22:47,580 --> 00:22:49,010
夏威夷的
From Hawaii.

403
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:51,370
-资浅参议员  -没错
- Junior Congressman? - That's right.

404
00:22:51,540 --> 00:22:54,630
我挺喜欢他  他人不错  很有野心
I like him. He's a good guy. He's ambitious.

405
00:22:54,940 --> 00:22:56,320
他给我开了很高的工资
He offered me a lot of money.

406
00:22:56,540 --> 00:22:58,580
-是吗  -22万年薪
- Yeah? - Two-twenty.

407
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:00,510
老天
Jesus.

408
00:23:02,310 --> 00:23:04,480
我在白宫永远挣不了这么多
That's more than I would ever make at the White House.

409
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:11,230
-这工作是你安排的吗  -不是
- You arrange the job? - No.

410
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:13,080
是总统安排的
Did the President?

411
00:23:14,050 --> 00:23:15,830
-你在说什么啊  -别糊弄我  赛斯
- What are you talking about? - Don't bullshit me, Seth.

412
00:23:15,830 --> 00:23:17,670
我头一次听说这事
This is the first I'm hearing about it.

413
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:21,680
夏威夷的资深参议员是谁
Who's the Senior Congressman from Hawaii?

414
00:23:24,740 --> 00:23:25,900
拨款委员会主席
Chair of Appropriations.

415
00:23:25,900 --> 00:23:28,010
我认识他  我只是一时想不起来
I know him, I'm just drawing a blank right now.

416
00:23:28,630 --> 00:23:30,680
不是他  是她
It's not him, it's a her.

417
00:23:31,520 --> 00:23:34,410
弗朗辛·谭纳卡  如果你不知道谭纳卡是谁
Francine Tenaka. And if you don't know who Tenaka is,

418
00:23:34,410 --> 00:23:36,690
那你根本不应该认识布拉德·帕蒂特
there's no reason you should know who Brad Petite is,

419
00:23:36,900 --> 00:23:38,860
也不该知道他人怎么样  是否有野心
or that he's ambitious or a good guy.

420
00:23:39,830 --> 00:23:42,500
这个工作机会是你或是总统安排的
This job offer came from you or the President.

421
00:23:43,350 --> 00:23:45,310
我告诉你并非如此
And I'm telling you that it didn't.

422
00:23:47,850 --> 00:23:49,060
我准备拒绝
Well, I'm turning it down.

423
00:23:50,370 --> 00:23:51,370
你转告总统
You tell the President that

424
00:23:51,370 --> 00:23:53,190
只要他需要我  我随时能回去工作
I'm ready to come back whenever he needs me.

425
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,580
我不需要辅助训练
I don't need training wheels.

426
00:24:10,530 --> 00:24:12,360
我需要你今晚上做做博奇的工作
I need you to work on Birch while you're here.

427
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:14,940
看能不能打听出潜在候选人名单
See if you can get that list of possible candidates.

428
00:24:15,380 --> 00:24:17,070
他被安排在了桌子边上
I don't think putting him down the far end of the table's

429
00:24:17,070 --> 00:24:18,740
好像不太想聊天呢
put him in a very chatty mood.

430
00:24:22,210 --> 00:24:25,390
冷藏  你是在说冷藏吗
Refrigeration. Are you talking about refrigeration?

431
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:27,760
不是  重新建立桥梁
No. Re-bridge nations.

432
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:29,200
要在两国之间
We need to re-bridgenate

433
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:31,050
重新建立桥梁  好增进信任
ourselves so we'll more trust each other.

434
00:24:31,050 --> 00:24:32,540
对吗  对的
Da? Yes.

435
00:24:33,490 --> 00:24:35,090
把修正案递交给国会吧
Let's get these amendments out of committee.

436
00:24:35,090 --> 00:24:36,600
不用全部递交  一部分就行
Not all of them, just some of them.

437
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:38,920
我要是干涉国会  议长肯定要发飙的
The Speaker would go ballistic if I started meddling in the House.

438
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:41,540
你可是潜在候选人  他不会轻易跟你翻脸
Not if it means he's going to battle with the presumptive nominee.

439
00:24:41,540 --> 00:24:43,210
他知道得靠谁吃饭
He knows where his bread is buttered.

440
00:24:43,210 --> 00:24:45,600
你休会任命了你老婆  逼我接受
You shove your wife's recess appointment down my throat,

441
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:46,410
现在还找我帮忙吗
now you want my help?

442
00:24:46,410 --> 00:24:47,930
总要有人担任那个职位
I had to fill the post.

443
00:24:47,930 --> 00:24:49,910
华盛顿哪没有外交专家
And you have a city full of career diplomats.

444
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:52,210
任命她简直就是打参议院的脸
Her appointment was a slap in the Senate's face.

445
00:24:52,210 --> 00:24:54,480
不要在一项任命上纠结
Let's not get hung up on appointments, all right?

446
00:24:54,660 --> 00:24:56,710
赫克特  你要我签署什么都可以
Hector, whatever you want me to sign, I'll sign.

447
00:24:56,710 --> 00:24:58,910
我不会拿否决要挟你
I will not hold a veto over your head.

448
00:24:58,910 --> 00:25:02,440
你可以随便否决  反正也是帮我们16年的忙
You can veto whatever you want. Just helps our case in 2016.

449
00:25:03,430 --> 00:25:04,380
失陪了
Excuse me.

450
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:14,100
哪个更醉人  是酒还是克莱尔·安德伍德
Which is more intoxicating, this wine or Claire Underwood?

451
00:25:16,340 --> 00:25:17,950
你经常用这句台词吗
How often do you use that line?

452
00:25:17,950 --> 00:25:20,870
-没你那句用得多  -哪句
- Not as often as you use yours. - Which line is that?

453
00:25:21,970 --> 00:25:23,580
"维克多  你在恋爱吗"
"Viktor, are you in love?"

454
00:25:26,790 --> 00:25:28,230
德斯科托总统说
President Descoteaux told me

455
00:25:28,230 --> 00:25:30,630
他来的时候你也问了这句话
you asked him the same thing when he was here.

456
00:25:32,690 --> 00:25:33,930
那晚我丈夫祝酒的时候
I believe my husband quoted

457
00:25:33,930 --> 00:25:35,910
好像引用了俄国作家的话
a Russian author the night he gave that toast.

458
00:25:35,910 --> 00:25:38,670
-我猜猜  托尔斯泰吗  -普希金
- Don't say, uh... Tolstoy? - Pushkin.

459
00:25:39,460 --> 00:25:41,430
"升华友谊的谎言
"A deception that elevates us

460
00:25:41,940 --> 00:25:44,280
要好过一堆无用的事实"
is dearer than a host of low truths."

461
00:25:45,900 --> 00:25:47,580
他才没那么说
He didn't make that toast.

462
00:25:48,440 --> 00:25:50,220
-是没有  -没有
- No, he didn't. - No, no.

463
00:25:51,940 --> 00:25:53,780
说实话  你是真了解普希金
Tell me, do you actually know your Pushkin,

464
00:25:53,780 --> 00:25:56,440
还是知道我来才研究的
or did you just study up before I arrived?

465
00:25:57,130 --> 00:25:58,300
重要吗
Does it really matter?

466
00:26:01,770 --> 00:26:04,660
他就是这么做事吗
So, this is what he does?

467
00:26:05,190 --> 00:26:06,850
让你来诱惑别人
He leaves the seduction to you.

468
00:26:07,260 --> 00:26:10,400
是不是有个词来着
Isn't there a... a word for that in English?

469
00:26:11,010 --> 00:26:13,600
-什么词  -拉皮条  是吗
- For what? - "Pimping," Yes?

470
00:26:14,050 --> 00:26:15,410
他在给你拉皮条
He's pimping you out.

471
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:19,250
你真有风度
How charming you are.

472
00:26:19,950 --> 00:26:20,820
谢谢
Thank you.

473
00:26:21,410 --> 00:26:24,450
据我的人说  你做第一夫人
And you make a much better First Lady than ambassador,

474
00:26:24,450 --> 00:26:26,120
比作大使强多了
from what my people tell me.

475
00:26:29,450 --> 00:26:30,590
开玩笑的
Only teasing.

476
00:26:31,520 --> 00:26:34,780
再来点酒  给大使的
More wine... for the ambassador.

477
00:26:35,310 --> 00:26:36,170
请吧
Please.

478
00:26:48,580 --> 00:26:50,590
我得回去一会儿
I'm gonna have to go in a couple minutes.

479
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:57,090
总统先生  给您的礼物
Mr. President, my gift for you.

480
00:26:57,990 --> 00:27:00,140
世上最好的伏特加
Best vodka in the world.

481
00:27:00,500 --> 00:27:02,220
莫斯科特供
Osobaya Sayanskaya.

482
00:27:03,840 --> 00:27:05,020
纯金瓶
Solid gold.

483
00:27:05,610 --> 00:27:08,690
每瓶75万美元
Each one of these bottles is 750,000.

484
00:27:10,130 --> 00:27:11,810
来敬杯酒
Now, a toast.

485
00:27:16,220 --> 00:27:18,880
敬友谊  敬美食
To friendship, to good food,

486
00:27:19,490 --> 00:27:24,290
敬列夫·托尔斯泰的名言
and to Leo Tolstoy, who said,

487
00:27:24,290 --> 00:27:27,450
"想要快乐  随心而动"
"If you want to be happy, be."

488
00:27:29,250 --> 00:27:30,090
干杯
Drink!

489
00:27:36,310 --> 00:27:39,040
然后闻一下面包
Now... you sniff your bread.

490
00:27:43,870 --> 00:27:45,010
说"好"
Say "ну".

491
00:27:45,300 --> 00:27:46,530
好
ну!

492
00:27:46,530 --> 00:27:47,560
再吹吹口哨
Then whistle.

493
00:27:48,980 --> 00:27:50,370
闻一下袖子
Sniff your sleeve.

494
00:27:51,180 --> 00:27:53,460
然后吃腌黄瓜
And... eat your pickle. -

495
00:27:55,350 --> 00:27:57,390
我们为什么要这么做呢
Now, why we do all this?

496
00:27:59,250 --> 00:28:00,360
谁也不知道
No one knows.

497
00:28:02,370 --> 00:28:03,240
再来一杯
Again!

498
00:28:03,670 --> 00:28:05,650
算了  总统先生
Oh, no. Now, Mr. President.

499
00:28:07,150 --> 00:28:09,870
你  副总统先生
Now, you, Mr. Vice President.

500
00:28:09,870 --> 00:28:10,800
敬酒词
A toast!

501
00:28:12,060 --> 00:28:16,120
敬我们两国之间
Uh, to, uh... further cooperation

502
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:20,340
进一步的合作  还有继续...
between our two countries and, uh... continued... uh...

503
00:28:21,320 --> 00:28:22,730
管他的  喝
Oh, hell. Here's how!

504
00:28:26,790 --> 00:28:27,620
再来
Again!

505
00:28:32,150 --> 00:28:35,420
到你了  安德伍德夫人
Now, you... Mrs. Underwood.

506
00:28:37,920 --> 00:28:41,140
敬佩特罗夫总统和他的
To President Petrov and his...

507
00:28:41,550 --> 00:28:42,850
小腌黄瓜
little pickle.

508
00:28:44,760 --> 00:28:45,650
喝
Drink!

