The Russians love to do that.

683
00:38:42,720 --> 00:38:43,570
晚安
Good night.

684
00:38:45,360 --> 00:38:47,530
我觉得不能相信他  凯茜
I don't think he's to be trusted, Cathy.

685
00:38:48,110 --> 00:38:51,200
尤其是今晚之后  让我不禁思考
Especially after tonight. And it made me think...

686
00:38:53,810 --> 00:38:54,680
继续说
Go on.

687
00:38:56,190 --> 00:38:59,030
这让我重新考虑了弗兰西斯的计划
It made me wonder about Francis' plan.

688
00:38:59,030 --> 00:39:03,640
我认为与佩特罗夫合作未必是好主意
I'm not sure that it's a good idea to be partnered with Petrov.

689
00:39:03,840 --> 00:39:07,320
而且我们还破坏了与以色列和巴勒斯坦的关系
In the meantime, we alienate Israel and Palestine.

690
00:39:10,160 --> 00:39:14,340
私下里告诉你  我也同意
Well... between you and me, I agree.

691
00:39:16,830 --> 00:39:17,850
过来坐
Sit with me.

692
00:39:19,550 --> 00:39:21,490
那你想采取什么不同的办法呢
What would you do differently?

693
00:39:23,960 --> 00:39:24,920
这个
Well...

694
00:39:27,030 --> 00:39:30,070
如果最终目标是向约旦河谷派军的话
If the goal is to get troops into the Jordan Valley,

695
00:39:30,070 --> 00:39:33,780
达到目标的办法可不止一种
well, then there's more than one way to skin that cat.

696
00:39:34,110 --> 00:39:35,800
多国部队吗
A multinational force?

697
00:39:36,400 --> 00:39:37,930
我倾向通过联合国
I would go through the UN.

698
00:39:38,980 --> 00:39:40,030
维和部队吗
Peacekeeping?

699
00:39:40,990 --> 00:39:42,980
但俄罗斯会否决的
You wouldn't get past Russia's veto.

700
00:39:43,660 --> 00:39:46,440
也许有个办法  但是...
There might be a way, but...

701
00:39:47,780 --> 00:39:50,840
那样你就有很重的任务了
you'd have a lot of responsibility on your shoulders.

702
00:39:51,970 --> 00:39:54,670
如果你能指点我  我相信我能处理好
Well, if you can give me guidance, I'm sure I can handle it.

703
00:39:56,970 --> 00:40:01,410
以前有联合维和决议案的先例
There is precedent with the Uniting for Peace Resolution.

704
00:40:01,410 --> 00:40:04,550
我们就是借这个  绕过苏俄发动了朝鲜战争
We used it to get around the Russians for the Korean War.

705
00:40:10,030 --> 00:40:12,790
-全部吗  -从波兰到英国
- The whole thing? - From Poland to the UK.

706
00:40:12,800 --> 00:40:15,070
我希望整个导弹防御系统都拆除
I want the entire missile defense system gone.

707
00:40:15,070 --> 00:40:17,960
你知道那是为了防御朝鲜和伊朗
You know that's there to defend against North Korea, against Iran.

708
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:20,090
但比起朝鲜伊朗  却离我国更近
And far closer to my borders than theirs.

709
00:40:20,090 --> 00:40:22,820
我只是希望你派几千部队进入约旦河谷
I'm asking for a few thousand troops in the Jordan Valley.

710
00:40:22,820 --> 00:40:25,290
你却要求我废除欧洲的防御系统
You're asking me to dismantle Europe's defense system.

711
00:40:25,290 --> 00:40:27,450
你真正的要求是让美国部队
What you're really asking for is American forces

712
00:40:27,450 --> 00:40:28,990
进入高加索南部
just south of the Caucasus.

713
00:40:29,340 --> 00:40:31,760
你肯定已经想好了战略规划
You must have a strategic play in mind.

714
00:40:31,770 --> 00:40:33,820
这是为了地区稳定
This is about stability in the region.

715
00:40:33,820 --> 00:40:36,810
你是想巩固在这个地区的地位吧
You're trying to consolidate your foothold in the region.

716
00:40:37,700 --> 00:40:40,940
黑海  哈萨克斯坦  车臣  克里米亚
The Black Sea, Kazakhstan, Chechnya, Crimea.

717
00:40:41,280 --> 00:40:44,890
拜托  别扯什么和平来侮辱我了
So, please... don't insult me with peace.

718
00:40:47,340 --> 00:40:49,750
无论你的战略目标是什么
Whatever your strategic goals may be,

719
00:40:51,320 --> 00:40:52,990
导弹防御系统是我的
the missile defense system is mine.

720
00:40:54,570 --> 00:40:58,400
维克多  我邀请你来华盛顿的目的很纯粹
Viktor, I invited you to Washington with pure intentions,

721
00:40:58,400 --> 00:41:01,520
就是为了我们能一起进餐  学习信任对方
so that we could break bread and learn to trust one another.

722
00:41:01,520 --> 00:41:04,880
弗兰西斯  一顿美妙的晚餐
Francis, I don't get softened up

723
00:41:04,880 --> 00:41:07,840
和与美丽的女士共舞不会让我心软的
by a nice dinner and dancing with a beautiful woman.

724
00:41:09,490 --> 00:41:10,890
你问我想要什么
You asked me what I want.

725
00:41:11,500 --> 00:41:13,140
我告诉你了
Well... I told you.

726
00:41:16,630 --> 00:41:17,700
这样吧
I'll tell you what.

727
00:41:18,160 --> 00:41:19,760
现在我要去睡会儿了
It's my turn to get some sleep.

728
00:41:19,760 --> 00:41:21,860
等头脑清醒点再处理这些事吧
Let's attack all this with a fresh mind.

729
00:41:21,860 --> 00:41:23,770
我们还没抽完雪茄呢
We've barely smoked our cigars.

730
00:41:25,570 --> 00:41:28,310
我们不是那种无节制的人  对吧
We're not men of excess, though, are we?

731
00:41:30,070 --> 00:41:31,000
不是吗
Aren't we?

732
00:41:35,480 --> 00:41:36,420
不是
No, no.

733
00:41:37,400 --> 00:41:38,490
不  你说得对
No, you're right.

734
00:41:41,430 --> 00:41:43,310
这一晚上抽得够多了
Enough smoke for one evening.

735
00:41:58,470 --> 00:41:59,970
你打算怎么办
What are you going to do?

736
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:02,330
不知道
I don't know.

737
00:42:03,640 --> 00:42:05,120
想办法与他妥协吧
Try to meet him halfway.

738
00:42:08,180 --> 00:42:09,620
凯茜和我聊了一会儿
Cathy and I were talking.

739
00:42:10,560 --> 00:42:13,030
也许以色列人和巴勒斯坦人是对的
Maybe the Israelis and the Palestinians are right.

740
00:42:13,030 --> 00:42:14,830
我们应该考虑从他们下手
We should consider starting with them.

741
00:42:15,260 --> 00:42:17,950
利用联合国向俄罗斯施压
Use the United Nations to put pressure on Russia.

742
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:20,940
-怎么施压  -联合维和
- How? - Uniting for Peace.

743
00:42:21,520 --> 00:42:22,680
让联合国大会推翻
General Assembly overrides

744
00:42:22,680 --> 00:42:24,780
俄罗斯在安理会投的否决票
a Russian veto in the Security Council.

745
00:42:26,000 --> 00:42:28,510
即便成功  也只会激怒他们
Well, that'll just antagonize them even if it works.

746
00:42:28,510 --> 00:42:29,370
何况不可能成功
And it won't.

747
00:42:29,380 --> 00:42:31,830
也许呢  凯茜似乎认为会成功
Well, it might work. Cathy seems to think it could.

748
00:42:32,440 --> 00:42:34,260
我以为你对这计划有信心
I thought you believed in this plan.

749
00:42:35,100 --> 00:42:38,110
我们只是在考虑别的选择
We were just... brainstorming alternatives.

750
00:42:38,560 --> 00:42:41,270
我付出了这么多努力  怎么能前功尽弃
Well, I've worked too hard on it just to abandon it.

751
00:42:43,240 --> 00:42:44,660
好吧  你知道怎么最好
Okay, you know best.

752
00:43:07,550 --> 00:43:08,460
你介意吗
Do you mind?

753
00:43:10,810 --> 00:43:11,600
什么
What?

754
00:43:12,090 --> 00:43:12,980
关灯
The light.

755
00:43:26,010 --> 00:43:27,150
弗兰西斯
Francis.

756
00:43:29,510 --> 00:43:30,560
他是个恶棍
He's a thug.

757
00:43:31,290 --> 00:43:32,940
很聪明  但也还是个恶棍
Smart, but he's still a thug.

758
00:43:33,240 --> 00:43:34,650
别向他屈服
Don't cower to him.

759
00:43:44,260 --> 00:43:45,230
在我的家乡
Where I come from,

760
00:43:45,230 --> 00:43:48,730
我们会把生鸡蛋放进番茄汁里  然后喝掉
we drop a raw egg into some tomato juice and drink that.

761
00:43:49,180 --> 00:43:50,850
还好我不来自你的家乡
Luckily, I don't come from there.

762
00:43:52,940 --> 00:43:54,170
那份工作很适合道格
That's a perfect job for Doug.

763
00:43:54,170 --> 00:43:56,010
真不明白他为什么拒绝
I can't imagine why he'd turn it down.

764
00:43:56,220 --> 00:43:57,670
他觉得是我们在背后安排的
He thinks we were behind it.

765
00:43:58,170 --> 00:44:00,300
我告诉他并没有  但恐怕他不相信我
I told him we weren't, but I don't think he believes me.

766
00:44:00,500 --> 00:44:02,170
说他不需要辅助训练
Said he doesn't need training wheels.

767
00:44:02,900 --> 00:44:05,450
我要你继续偶尔去看看他
Well, I want you to still stop in from time to time and see him.

768
00:44:05,460 --> 00:44:06,280
是  先生
Yes, sir.

769
00:44:07,630 --> 00:44:10,120
国防部长来了吗  让他进来
Is the Secretary of Defense here? Send him in.

770
00:44:13,050 --> 00:44:14,920
-总统先生  -我们没多少时间
- Mr. President. - We don't have much time.

771
00:44:14,920 --> 00:44:17,510
佩特罗夫90分钟后到  我们得谈欧洲的情况
Petrov gets here in 90 minutes. We need to talk Europe.

772
00:45:00,400 --> 00:45:02,800
答案是可以
The answer is yes.

773
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:05,890
可以接受你的部分但并非全部要求
To some, not all, of what you asked.

774
00:45:07,230 --> 00:45:07,810
好吧
I see.

775
00:45:07,810 --> 00:45:10,280
我准备对导弹防御系统进行大规模削减
I'm prepared to scale back significantly.

776
00:45:10,290 --> 00:45:14,960
我得先跟我的团队及我们的北约同盟国商量下
Now, I have to speak to my team first and my allies in NATO,

777
00:45:14,960 --> 00:45:17,520
但我相信我们可以在波兰和捷克共和国
but I'm confident that we can do something meaningful

778
00:45:17,520 --> 00:45:19,580
作出重要调整
in Poland and the Czech Republic.

779
00:45:19,580 --> 00:45:22,080
我们双方可以就细节做进一步协商
Now, our people can work out the specifics.

780
00:45:22,080 --> 00:45:25,190
但无论我们达成怎样的共识
And whatever it is we decide and agree on,

781
00:45:25,190 --> 00:45:27,280
都不能让公众知晓
the public cannot know.

782
00:45:31,940 --> 00:45:35,470
我醒来时满嘴都是昨晚抽过的雪茄味
I woke up with the taste of those cigars in my mouth.

783
00:45:36,120 --> 00:45:38,460
让我想到了古巴导弹危机和肯尼迪
Thinking of Cuba and Kennedy.

784
00:45:39,110 --> 00:45:42,640
{\pos(382,286)}{\an3}古巴导弹危机时
美国最终从土耳其撤军
比苏联晚一些  而且是秘密撤军
表面上来看是这场危机的胜利者

785
00:45:39,120 --> 00:45:40,700
我可不会像赫鲁晓夫
I won't be humiliated the way

786
00:45:40,700 --> 00:45:42,640
在土耳其导弹问题上那样被羞辱
Khrushchev was with Turkey.

787
00:45:43,440 --> 00:45:44,810
你不能将我的提议
Well, you can't possibly compare

788
00:45:44,810 --> 00:45:46,850
与当时的事件相提并论
what I'm proposing to what happened then.

789
00:45:46,850 --> 00:45:48,860
只有你同意对外宣布
I can only consider a partial scale-back

790
00:45:48,860 --> 00:45:50,230
我才会接受部分削减
if you announce it.

791
00:45:52,830 --> 00:45:55,040
这场新闻发布会是关于约旦河谷问题
This press conference is about the Jordan Valley.

792
00:45:55,040 --> 00:45:57,100
调整导弹防御系统的重点是削减
The most important thing about the missiles is the scale-back,

793
00:45:57,100 --> 00:45:57,880
不是公关
not the PR.

794
00:45:57,880 --> 00:46:00,670
我的人民需要知道我不是空手而归
My people would know I walked away with something.

795
00:46:00,670 --> 00:46:04,830
而且对外宣布后  我就能逼你信守诺言
And, by announcing it, I can keep you to your word.

796
00:46:04,840 --> 00:46:08,080
我可是做出了相当大的让步  维克多
I am more than meeting you halfway, Viktor.

797
00:46:14,410 --> 00:46:17,860
你知道苏联解体最大快人心之处是什么吗
You know what the best part of the Fall of the Soviet Union was?

798
00:46:19,150 --> 00:46:20,200
是汽车
The cars.

799
00:46:21,660 --> 00:46:23,910
你坐过拉达牌汽车吗
Have you ever been in, um... a Lada?

800
00:46:24,610 --> 00:46:25,970
拉达  没有
Lada? No, I haven't.

801
00:46:25,970 --> 00:46:28,560
没有吗  那是世上最烂的车
No? Oh. It's the worst car ever built.

802
00:46:28,820 --> 00:46:30,440
很小  很袖珍的一辆车
Tiny, little thing, you know.

803
00:46:30,440 --> 00:46:34,230
车开过坑颠一下  你的头就会撞到车顶
Your head would hit the ceiling when you hit a pothole.

804
00:46:34,480 --> 00:46:36,640
暖气永远不制热
And the heat never worked.

805
00:46:37,320 --> 00:46:38,600
还没有空调
And no air conditioning.

806
00:46:38,600 --> 00:46:41,620
大夏天皮肤都要粘到座位上
You know, your skin would stick to the seats in the summer.

807
00:46:41,620 --> 00:46:43,610
简直是可移动的棺材
It was a coffin on wheels.

808
00:46:43,680 --> 00:46:48,550
但苏联解体后  就能买到雷克萨斯
But then, after the Fall, we got the Lexus.

809
00:46:49,750 --> 00:46:52,730
有空调  自动车窗
Temperature control. Automatic windows.

810
00:46:53,020 --> 00:46:54,830
而且空间很大
And so much room.

811
00:46:54,830 --> 00:46:58,410
我第一次上我前妻  就是在一辆雷克萨斯里
First time I fucked my ex-wife, in a Lexus.

812
00:46:58,590 --> 00:47:00,150
在拉达里你想都不要想
You could never do that in a Lada.

813
00:47:00,150 --> 00:47:00,980
空间根本不够
No space.

814
00:47:02,540 --> 00:47:04,040
现在情况是这样  总统先生
You see, Mr. President.

815
00:47:05,470 --> 00:47:06,960
我想要雷克萨斯
I want the Lexus.

816
00:47:08,530 --> 00:47:10,680
你却向我推销拉达
And you're trying to sell me a Lada.

817
00:47:37,270 --> 00:47:39,390
我去让你的车队来接你
I'll have them bring your motorcade around.

818
00:47:42,880 --> 00:47:44,820
但还有新闻发布会
But the... press conference.

819
00:47:47,390 --> 00:47:48,310
对啊
Right!

820
00:47:49,680 --> 00:47:51,330
我忘得一干二净
I'd completely forgotten.

821
00:47:52,650 --> 00:47:55,290
不过今天不做新闻发布会也不要紧
But I think we're gonna be okay without one today.

822
00:47:57,230 --> 00:47:59,350
回程一路顺风  总统先生
Have a safe journey home, Mr. President.

823
00:48:08,880 --> 00:48:11,750
多谢你的款待  总统先生
Thank you for your hospitality, Mr. President.

824
00:48:22,010 --> 00:48:23,610
给我接国务卿
Give me the Secretary of State.

825
00:48:38,030 --> 00:48:39,810
总统将单独发表讲话
The President will be speaking alone.

826
00:48:39,810 --> 00:48:41,450
不举行联合新闻发布会
No joint conference.

827
00:48:43,590 --> 00:48:45,720
总统很快就来
The President will be out shortly.

828
00:48:51,870 --> 00:48:54,530
昨晚  我有幸在白宫招待了
Last night, I had the pleasure of hosting

829
00:48:54,540 --> 00:48:57,160
几位非常尊贵的宾客
some very special guests here at the White House.

830
00:48:57,710 --> 00:48:59,510
几位真正的俄罗斯爱国者
True Russian patriots

831
00:48:59,510 --> 00:49:02,540
他们展现了他们国家最优良的美德
who exhibit the very best that their country has to offer.

832
00:49:03,210 --> 00:49:05,820
他们的名字是  娜迪亚·托伦科尼卡瓦
Their names: Nadya Tolokonnikova,

833
00:49:05,960 --> 00:49:09,450
玛莎·艾柳金纳和彼得·韦奇洛夫
Masha Alyokhina and Pyotr Verzilov.

834
00:49:09,700 --> 00:49:11,220
你们应该已经知道
As you're all aware,

835
00:49:11,300 --> 00:49:13,330
他们敢于挑战佩特罗夫总统
they stood up to President Petrov,

836
00:49:13,460 --> 00:49:17,230
并强迫他倾听他不愿听到的真相
and forced him to listen to the truths that he didn't want to hear.

837
00:49:18,920 --> 00:49:22,300
这令我深受震撼
And, well, that had a profound effect on me.

838
00:49:22,770 --> 00:49:24,100
因为这让我意识到
Because it made me realize

839
00:49:24,100 --> 00:49:25,820
我也要勇于与他抗衡
that I need to stand up to him as well.

840
00:49:25,820 --> 00:49:27,600
我们的国家也一样
As does our country.

841
00:49:28,050 --> 00:49:29,550
我邀请总统来访
When I invited the President here,

842
00:49:29,550 --> 00:49:32,350
是旨在结交盟友
I set out hoping to find a partner.

843
00:49:32,650 --> 00:49:36,580
但佩特罗夫总统的要求让我明白
But the demands that President Petrov made proves to me

844
00:49:36,910 --> 00:49:39,730
和平并非他的第一诉求
that peace is not a priority for him.

845
00:49:40,150 --> 00:49:43,390
和平不该通过买卖取得
Peace should not have to be bought.

846
00:49:43,630 --> 00:49:46,330
和平本就该足矣
Peace should be its own reward,

847
00:49:46,480 --> 00:49:48,100
不论他是否是我们的盟友
and we will achieve it,

848
00:49:48,250 --> 00:49:50,270
我们终会迎来和平
with or without him.

849
00:49:50,310 --> 00:49:51,620
非常感谢
Thank you very much.

850
00:49:52,480 --> 00:49:54,600
你知道怎样能绕过俄国
You have thoughts on how to bypass Russia.

851
00:49:54,670 --> 00:49:58,220
就是要让俄国在联合国安理会的否决票无效
The idea is to negate Russia's veto in the Security Council.

852
00:49:58,230 --> 00:50:00,920
我会让大使向您介绍我们的想法
I'll let the Ambassador tell you what we have in mind.

853
